# Definition Function from A onto B

A function  $\phi$  from a set  $A$  to a set  $B$  is said to be onto  $B$  if each element of  $B$  is the image of at least one element of  $A$ . In symbols,  $\phi : A \to B$  is onto if for each  $b$  in  $B$  there is at least one  $a$  in  $A$  such that  $\phi(a) = b$ . See Figure 0.5.

