Consider the equilateral triangle inscribed in the regular hexagon as shown in the figure below. Let  $F$  be a reflection that passes through one vertex of the triangle to the opposite vertex of the hexagon. Then  $K = \{R_0, R_{120}, R_{240}, F, R_{120}F, R_{240}F\}$  is a subgroup of  $D_6$ .

