(see Exercise 7), and  $D_{\infty} / H$  satisfies the defining relations for  $D_{i}$  (use Exercise 9 with  $x = aH$  and  $y = abH$ ). In particular,  $G$  is finite—an impossibility.

If  $h = (ab)^i a$ , then

$$
H = (a b) ^ {i} a H = (a b) ^ {i} H a H,
