Erdős was born on March 26, 1913, in Hungary. Both of his parents were high school mathematics teachers. Erdős, a Jew, left Hungary in 1934 at the age of 21 because of the rapid rise of anti-Semitism in Europe. For the rest of his life he traveled incessantly, rarely pausing more than a month in any one place, giving lectures for small honoraria

